cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with deep learning techniques for point cloud data in 3D computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that involves computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes new point cloud classification neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper deals with real-world point cloud object dataset based on scanned indoor scene data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also identifies three key open problems for point cloud object classification, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with 3D object classification and segmentation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics).
